{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:31:30.145342+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, all write attempts are failing with a 403 permission error — the GitHub token doesn't have write access to this repository. I'll document the exact changes I prepared so they can be applied by someone with the necessary permissions.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Issue #6: \"Update the safe scan profile\"\n\n### Analysis\n\nThe issue requests adding explicit **service/version detection** to the safe local scan profile while keeping scope restricted to localhost.\n\nLooking at the current state:\n- `scan_profiles/safe_local.yml` — already has `-sV` in the raw options list, but lacks a dedicated configuration key documenting that service/version detection is a deliberate profile feature.\n- `scripts/run_safe_scan.sh` — already passes `-sV` to nmap, but doesn't explain why.\n\n### Prepared Changes\n\n#### 1. `scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`\n\n**Current:**\n```yaml\nname: safe-local\nscope: localhost-only\noptions:\n  - -sV\n  - --top-ports\n  - \"100\"\nforbidden:\n  - public_ip_ranges\n  - aggressive_external_scans\n```\n\n**Proposed:**\n```yaml\nname: safe-local\nscope: localhost-only\nservice_version: true\noptions:\n  - -sV\n  - --top-ports\n  - \"100\"\nforbidden:\n  - public_ip_ranges\n  - aggressive_external_scans\n```\n\n**What changed:** Added `service_version: true` as an explicit profile-level configuration key, making it clear that service/version detection is intentionally enabled.\n\n#### 2. `scripts/run_safe_scan.sh`\n\n**Current:**\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\nTARGET=${1:-127.0.0.1}\ncase \"$TARGET\" in\n  127.0.0.1|localhost) ;;\n  *) echo \"Refusing to scan non-local target: $TARGET\" >&2; exit 2 ;;\nesac\nnmap -sV --top-ports 100 -oX reports/local_scan.xml \"$TARGET\"\n```\n\n**Proposed:**\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\nTARGET=${1:-127.0.0.1}\ncase \"$TARGET\" in\n  127.0.0.1|localhost) ;;\n  